almon Falls Rd.\r\n87.57|Right onto Lake Hills Dr. (sharp turn)\r\n88.67|Left at STOP (Bonita Dr.)\r\n88.82|Right onto Loma Verde Dr.\r\n88.97|Left on Encina Dr.\r\n89.27|Park where you can at 580 Encina Dr.','\r',char(13)),'\n',char(10)),replace(replace('Bonus Questions:\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>The Bayley House is on what road?\r\n<li>What is the name of the ranch that breeds Egyptian Arabian show horses?\r\n<li>On what road do you find a lighthouse?\r\n<li>What is the elevation of Kelsey?\r\n</ol>','\r',char(13)),'\n',char(10)),replace(replace('5.89| -> Picture 1 - Well & Bridge on Right\r\n8.21| -> Picture 2 - Old lean-to Right\r\n10.19| -> Picture 3 - Old rail road tracks that curve to the left\r\n12.49| -> Picture 4 - windmill on left\r\n13.57| -> Picture 5 - Small barn with windows on right\r\n16.14| -> Picture 6 - Cattle ramp\r\n16.59| -> Picture 7 - Mailbox on left\r\n21,40| -> Picture 8 - Old house on left past RRxing\r\n25.03| -> Picture 9 - Gazzebo on left\r\n34.31| -> Picture 10 - Vineyard House Sign on left\r\n34.94| -> Picture 11 - Chinese store on left\r\n41.64| -> Picture 12 - Old truck on right\r\n\r\nBonus answers:\r\nBayley house is on Hwy. 49\r\n"Aralia - Egyptian Arabian show horses" \r\nThe lighthouse is on Shoofly Rd.\r\nKelsey is at 1920 ft.','\r',char(13)),'\n',char(10)),'',NULL,X'',NULL,0.0,'',0,0);
INSERT INTO routes VALUES(50,' President''s Day Run','2006-02-26','Robin & Jeanne George','A leisurely 80-mile drive through the Amador County foothills.  Start at the McDonald''s at the corner of White Rock Rd. and Sunrise Blvd.  End in Plymouth for lunch.',replace(replace('Right on White Rock Rd.\r\nLeft on Grantline Rd.\r\nRight on Latrobe Rd. - regroup area by dancing deer sign\r\nLeft on Hwy 49 - regroup area by Carbondale Rd. sign\r\nRight on Willow Creek Rd.\r\nLeft on Tonzi Rd. (Road 44) - ONE LANE ROAD: USE CAUTION\r\nRight on Ione Rd. - Back cutoff\r\nLeft on Spanish St.\r\nRight on Hwy 49\r\nLeft into alley between Community Center and the fire house (red color) - bathroom stop\r\nLeft on Church St. - regroup area by the red buildings\r\nLeft on Pine Gulch Rd. - by Daffodil Hill turn left sign\r\nRight at stop sign - merges with Shake Ridge Rd.\r\nLeft at stop sign at Daffodil Hill\r\nLeft on Fiddletown Rd. - look for "Fiddletown 10 miles" sign on the right, turn just after\r\nStraight into the town of Plymouth\r\nIncahoots restaurant is on the left at 9486 Main St.','\r',char(13)),'\n',char(10)),replace(replace('To return home:\r\nExit left, follow Main St. to Old Sacramento Rd and turn right on Latrobe Rd.  This takes you back to El Dorado Hills and Hwy 50.  You may also go back to Hwy 49 and follow it north to Placerville and Hwy 50 (longer route).','\r',char(13)),'\n',char(10)),'','',NULL,X'',NULL,0.0,'',0,0);
INSERT INTO routes VALUES(51,'July 4th 2006 Poker Run','2006-07-04','Bob & Genny Paauwe',replace(replace('A poker run that starts in Newcastle in the Dennys parking lot (I-80 at Newcastle exit). Collect seven cards at designated card stops along a predetermined route. \r\n<p>\r\nHigh and low hands will win prizes. Aces are high. \r\n<p>\r\n<b>NOTE:</b> We suggest you fill up before leaving the Auburn area. Gas stations are scarce thereafter. Please zero out your odometer after picking up your poker card. A nice spot for a picnic is Loon Lake, about 1 hour, 45 minutes into the route. \r\n<br>\r\n','\r',char(13)),'\n',char(10)),replace(replace('-|CARD STOP #1: START\r\n-|\r\n-|You will get a card just before you start the route.\r\n-|\r\n0.0|Exit Dennys parking lot onto Newcastle Road.\r\n0.1|RIGHT at SIGNAL onto Indian Hill Road.\r\n2.4|LEFT at SIGNAL onto Auburn Folsom Road.\r\n3.0|RIGHT onto Sacramento Street (signal).\r\n3.6|RIGHT at 3rd STOP onto Pacific Ave.\r\n4.1|RIGHT into Auburn Area Recreation and Park District parking lot.\r\n-|\r\n-|CARD STOP #2: Auburn Dam Overlook\r\n-|\r\n-|Envelope with cards can be found taped to the back of the pay telephone. Take a look at where Auburn Lake would have been if the Auburn dam project had been completed. Restrooms available.\r\n-|\r\n0.0|RIGHT out of parking area onto Pacific Ave. (becomes Pleasant Ave. after RXR).\r\n0.45|RIGHT at 2nd STOP onto High Street.\r\n1.25|STRAIGHT at SIGNALS toward Cool and Placerville (Hwy 49 south). Go down canyon.\r\n3.50|Turn RIGHT at bottom onto bridge, staying on Hwy 49 south.\r\n7.2|LEFT at STOP onto Hwy 193 toward Georgetown.\r\n19.5|LEFT at STOP onto Main Street (Georgetown).\r\n-|NOTE: Public restrooms are sometimes unlocked at the park just past town on your right (Harkeness St.). Near the mini-railroad. An alternative is the baseball park just outside Georgetown. \r\n|Continue STRAIGHT, road becomes Wentworth Springs Road.\r\n36.1|RIGHT into Stumpy Meadows Lake Boat Ramp parking area.\r\n-|\r\n-|CARD STOP #3: Stumpy Meadows Lake\r\n-|\r\n-|Envelope with cards can be found on the back of the information signs at entrance to parking area.\r\n-|Stumpy Meadows is a popular place for summertime camping, boating and swimming. Restrooms are available.\r\n-|\r\n0.0|RIGHT out of parking area onto Wentworth Springs Road.\r\n14.5|LEFT at STOP onto Ice House Road (toward Loon Lake).\r\n15.8|RIGHT onto Wentworth Springs Road.\r\n20.25|RIGHT at El Dorado National Forest Recreation Area Loon Lake sign.\r\n20.7| STRAIGHT, entering day use parking area.\r\n-|\r\n-|CARD STOP #4: Loon Lake\r\n-|\r\n-|Envelope with cards can be found on the message board. \r\n-|Loon Lake is surrounded in barren alpine beauty. Grey granite slabs, icy cold water and whispering pines welcome you to this picnic spot. Restrooms available -- use them! It is your last chance until the end of the event.\r\n-|\r\n0.0|Leave parking area the way you came in.\r\n0.45|LEFT at STOP toward Hwy 50.\r\n4.9|LEFT at STOP onto Wentworth Springs Road towards Hwy 50/Placerville.\r\n29.0|RIGHT onto Hwy 50 toward Placerville and Sacramento.\r\n29.1|Pull off in the wide spot just past the river at the Historical Marker.\r\n-|\r\n-|CARD STOP #5: Historical Marker #705\r\n-|\r\n-|Envelope with cards can be found on the back of the guardrail. \r\n-|Learn about Pony Express Trail history here. No restrooms\r\n-|\r\n0.0|Continue West on Hwy 50 toward Placerville and Sacramento.\r\n21.7|STRAIGHT through Placerville, staying on Hwy 50 (several signals).\r\n27.1|RIGHT exiting Hwy 50 at Greenstone Road.\r\n27.3|RIGHT onto Greenstone Road.\r\n28.3|LEFT at STOP onto Green Valley Road.\r\n31.0|LEFT at STOP, staying on Green Valley Road.\r\n31.6|RIGHT onto Green Valley Road.\r\n32.5|RIGHT onto Deer Valley Road.\r\n32.6|RIGHT into Post Office parking lot (past the Fire Department).\r\n-|\r\n-|CARD STOP #6: Rescue, California\r\n-|\r\n-|Envelope with cards can be found on post office message board.\r\n-|Often the Rescue Fire Dept. has a July 4th event here. Enjoy the shade before continuing on the last leg of the poker run. No restrooms unless you make friends with the firemen.\r\n-|\r\n0.0|LEFT out of parking lot onto Deer Valley Road.\r\n0.1|RIGHT at STOP onto Green Valley Road.\r\n|Continue STRAIGHT at next 4 SIGNALS.\r\n\r\n-|RIGHT onto Francisco Dr.\r\n-|LEFT at first opportunity into strip mall.\r\n-|Look for Round Table Pizza.\r\n\r\n-|CARD STOP #7: Round Table Pizza, 2222 Francisco Dr., El Dorado Hills\r\n\r\n-|END','\r',char(13)),'\n',char(10)),replace(replace('The standard ranking of poker hands are:\r\n<ul>\r\n\r\n<li>Five of a kind: Five cards of the same rank (only possible in games with wild cards) Example: A&#9824; A&#9827; A&#9829; A&#9830; Joker\r\n<li>Straight flush: Five cards in sequence and of the same suit. Example: Q&#9830; J&#9830; 10&#9830; 9&#9830; 8&#9830; (An ace-high straight flush is often called a "royal flush", and is the highest hand possible without widecards).    <li>Four of a kind: A hand with four cards of the same rank. Example: 4&#9827; 4&#9830; 4&#9829; 4&#9824; 9&#9829;\r\n<li>Full house: A hand with three cards of one rank and two of another. Example: 8&#9827; 8&#9830; 8&#9824; K&#9829; K&#9824; (Often described as the three-of-a-kind rank full of the pair rank. The example is eights full of kings)\r\n<li>Flush: Five cards of the same suit. Example: K&#9824; J&#9824; 8&#9824; 4&#9824; 3&#9824;\r\n<li>Straight: Five cards in sequence. (The ace can be considered higher than the king or lower than the two.) Example: 5&#9830; 4&#9829; 3&#9824; 2&#9830; A&#9830;\r\n<li>Three of a kind: Three cards of the same rank. Example: 7&#9827; 7&#9829; 7&#9824; K&#9830; 2&#9824;\r\n<li>Two pair: Two cards of one rank, two of another. Example: A&#9827; A&#9830; 8&#9829; 8&#9824; Q&#9824;\r\n<li>One pair: Two cards of the same rank. Example: 9&#9829; 9&#9824; A&#9827; J&#9824; 4&#9829;\r\n<li>High card: Also known as a no pair hand. The following example is considered Ace high. Example: A&#9830; 10&#9830; 9&#9824; 5&#9827; 4&#9827;\r\n</ul>\r\nThe hands are ranked in this order because of their relative probabilities, with rarer hands ranking above more common hands. See also Poker probability. In addition, all 5 card poker hands can be collapsed down to 7,462 distinct equivalence classes. For example, there are 24 different ways to create an Aces over Kings Full House hand, but since they all hold the same poker ranking value, they can be collapsed into the same equivalence class. In this way, all 2,598,960 unique five card poker hands can be shrunk down to just 7,462 distinct classes of hands.','\r',char(13)),'\n',char(10)),'','',NULL,X'',NULL,0.0,'',0,0);
