aying on Hwy 49.\r\n2.00|STRAIGHT at SIGNAL.\r\n2.50|STRAIGHT at SIGNAL.\r\n2.90|STRAIGHT at SIGNAL\r\n6.50|RIGHT on Old 49 towards Amador City / Sutter Creek. (Sharp Right)\r\n9.80|LEFT onto Church St. in Sutter Creek (Just before divided road begins).  NOTE: Do not use the Church St. in Amador City!\r\n12.30|LEFT onto Pine Gulch Rd.\r\n12.90|STRAIGHT onto Shake Ridge Rd.\r\n20.80|LEFT onto Hale Rd.\r\n27.00|LEFT onto Fiddletown Rd.\r\n34.30|STRAIGHT at YIELD.\r\n34.80|STRAIGHT at STOP, cross Hwy 49 onto Main St. (Plymouth)\r\n|Main St. becomes Old Sacramento Rd.\r\n40.00|RIGHT at STOP onto Latrobe Rd.\r\n50.00|If you want to pre-order a pizza, now might be a good time!\r\n54.70|Drive under Hwy 50 - Latrobe Rd. becomes El Dorado Hills Blvd. DO NOT ENTER HWY. 50!\r\n58.30|LEFT at STOP onto Francisco Dr.\r\n58.90|STRAIGHT at SIGNAL (Green Valley Rd.)\r\n59.00|LEFT at SIGNAL into parking lot (Finish!)\r\n-|The Finish is at Round Table Pizza, 2222 Francisco Dr., El Dorado Hills.  (916) 933-4300\r\n','\r',char(13)),'\n',char(10)),replace(replace('<br style="page-break-before:always;">\r\nAnswer the following questions as you make your way along the route. The answers to all questions are visible from your vehicle when traveling in the correct direction on the route.<p>\r\nA STOP is defined as a red and white octagonal sign with the word "STOP" that controls your progress along the route.<p>\r\nA "Bump" is a raised section of road created specifically to slow your progress along the route.<p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>What color is the Incahoots building?\r\n<li>At what mileage do you encounter "Hidden Springs Water"?\r\n<li>How many STOP signs are there along the route?\r\n<li>What is the zip code of the town of Campo Seco, CA?\r\n<li>How many archery ranges did you see along the route?\r\n<li>What is the number of the locomotive that sits in the center of Ione?\r\n<li>Sutter Creek is known as _____________?\r\n<li>At what mileage do you encounter White Rock Rd.''s namesake?\r\n<l