INSERT INTO routes VALUES(69,'SacWEVs Passenger Swap Road Rally ','2024-04-27',' Genny Paauwe ',replace(replace('Enjoy a day out exploring the foothills surrounding Sacramento with fellow WEVs. The passenger swap road rally will feature gold rush history, views of California waterways and feats of engineering, and a unique stop sure to have you humming "Folsom Prison Blues."\r\n<p>\r\nArrive with at least 100 miles on your car, some money for a Mexican food lunch, and a sense of fun and adventure.\r\n<p>\r\nNote: There are a variety of charging opportunities nearby the start location, including a Tesla Supercharger, Charge Point (2 locations) and Electrify America.\r\n<p>\r\nSTART: Noah''s Bagels, 210 Palladio Pkwy., Folsom, 95630 (corner of East Bidwell St. and Iron Point Rd.)\r\n<p>\r\nMeet at Noah''s Bagels at 9:45 a.m. A drivers meeting will be held promptly at 10 a.m.\r\n<p>\r\nTotal rally mileage: 81.1 miles\r\n','\r',char(13)),'\n',char(10)),replace(replace('-|Drive through the parking lot to the front of Whole Foods. Straight at Whole Foods to the parking lot exit onto East Bidwell St.\r\n\r\n0.0|Zero out your odometer as you turn RIGHT onto East Bidwell St.\r\n0.05|LEFT onto Iron Point Rd. at SIGNAL (it''s the first left and comes up quickly; use both left turn lanes)\r\n1.4|LEFT onto Empire Ranch Rd. at SIGNAL (Becomes Sophia Pkwy. after E. Natoma St.)\r\n3.0| Stay in right lane at E. Natoma St. to continue straight \r\n(signal)\r\n4.8|Note view of Folsom Lake on left near Elmores Wy. (stop sign)\r\n5.2|RIGHT onto Green Valley Rd. at SIGNAL \r\n10.5|Note that this was once part of the Pony Express Trail. You''ll see an old farmhouse that was a stop for riders to exchange horses.\r\n15.5|LEFT at T intersection (signal), staying on Green Valley Rd. (North Shingle Rd. is to the right)\r\n15.7|Note Sleepy Hollow to the right where on Halloween a headless horseman once rode through the neighborhood.\r\n16.1|Continue STRAIGHT onto Lotus Rd. (do not follow Green Valley Rd. to right)\r\n19.5|STRAIGHT at Gold Hill Rd.\r\n19.7|RIGHT onto Thompson Hill Rd. (use caution: this is a skinny, windy road)\r\n22.0|LEFT at T intersection onto Cold Springs Rd.; Welcome to Coloma!\r\n23.2|LEFT onto Monument Rd., Hwy 153. Look for Marshall Monument sign. This is California''s shortest state highway.\r\n-| \r\n-|Note that you''re heading up to the James Marshall Monument that overlooks the American River below. The statue points to the spot in the river where the first gold nugget was discovered in 1848, forever changing the future of California.\r\n-|  \r\n23.6|We''ll briefly stop at the parking area if there is space, then drive the one-way loop around the monument. This is a fee area, so we won''t stay long, and not at all if there is a State Parks vehicle nearby!\r\n-|  \r\n23.8|Once around the monument, follow the one way sign to the LEFT down Marshall Park Way toward Marshall Cabin. Use caution; this is a skinny, twisty one-way street and sometimes there are people hiking.\r\n-|  \r\n24.2|LEFT at STOP onto High St.\r\n24.3|At sharp left, becomes Back St.\r\n24.3|Quick RIGHT onto Brewery St.\r\n24.4|LEFT onto Hwy 49 northbound (T intersection)\r\n25.3|Cross the American River\r\n25.4|Make first LEFT into driveway business area; park near Sierra Rizing Bakery and Coffee House\r\n-|  \r\n-|<b>PASSENGER SWAP #1: Lotus [10 MINUTE BREAK]</b>\r\n-|  \r\n0.0|Exit parking area and zero out your odometer as you turn LEFT onto Hwy 49 northbound\r\n6.5|Go through Pilot Hill\r\n10.4|At STOP continue STRAIGHT on Hwy 49 (where it meets Hwy 193 in Cool)\r\n-|Now comes the fun part! This twisty downhill run will give you views of the American River canyon and confluence. This area is called The Foresthill Divide. Look for views of Foresthill Bridge, the highest bridge by deck height in California, the fourth highest in the United States, and among the seventy highest in the world at 730 feet above the river.\r\n14.0|Cross the American River\r\n14.0|RIGHT at STOP onto Old Foresthill Rd. (T intersection)\r\n14.3|Cross the American River\r\n17.4|LEFT at STOP onto Foresthill Rd. (T intersection)\r\n19.4|Cross Foresthill Bridge\r\n20.6|Stay in middle lane at Lincoln Way signal\r\n20.7|Cross Interstate 80; becomes Auburn Ravine Rd.\r\n21.0|Cross RR tracks\r\n22.0|RIGHT at STOP onto Marguerite Mine Rd.\r\n22.5|RIGHT at SIGNAL onto Grass Valley Hwy (Hwy 49 north)\r\n23.6|RIGHT at SIGNAL onto New Airport Rd.\r\n26.6|Immediate LEFT into parking area for El Tapatio Mexican restaurant, 2100 Grass Valley Hwy., Auburn, CA 95603\r\n-|  \r\n-|<b>LUNCH STOP + PASSENGER SWAP #2: Auburn</b>\r\n-|  \r\n-|After lunch, leave the restaurant via the same driveway toward New Airport Rd. \r\n-|  \r\n0.0|Zero out your odometer as turn RIGHT onto New Airport Rd.\r\n0.05|Immediate LEFT at SIGNAL onto Grass Valley Hwy (Hwy 49 south)\r\n-|Stay in right lane on Hwy 49\r\n1.0|RIGHT onto Nevada St. just before signal\r\n1.1|RIGHT at STOP onto Nevada St. (T intersection)\r\n1.9|RIGHT at SIGNAL onto Mt. Vernon Rd.\r\n2.1|RIGHT onto Merry Knoll Rd. (this is a residential neighborhood)\r\n2.3|At Y, stay RIGHT on Merry Knoll Rd.\r\n2.4|RIGHT into gravel parking area; park\r\n-|Short break to view Wise Forebay Preserve\r\n-|  \r\n-|Note: The 17-acre Wise Forebay Preserve is part of the Placer Land Trust. The area is owned and operated as part of PG&E''s hydroelectric scheme. The waterway that feeds the forebay is a modern version of the very long Wise Canal and is one of the many built during the mid- to late-1800s around Placer County. The canals provided water for gold mining as well as and farming operations farther down the hill, and now energy to millions of households.\r\n-|  \r\n2.4|Exit gravel parking area to the RIGHT\r\n-|Merry Knoll Rd. makes a loop\r\n3.0|RIGHT at the Y, staying on Merry Knoll Rd.\r\n3.2|LEFT at STOP onto Mt. Vernon Rd.\r\n3.4|RIGHT at SIGNAL onto Nevada St.\r\n4.3|LEFT at STOP onto Placer St. (DO NOT CONTINUE STRAIGHT, o